research_results.parameter_optimization:
Here's a comprehensive optimization framework for the Ichimoku Cloud Momentum strategy:

```json
{
    "strategy_name": "Ichimoku Cloud Momentum",
    "optimization_parameters": {
        "ichimoku_parameters": {
            "conversion_line_period": {
                "range": [9, 20],
                "default": 9,
                "sensitivity": "high"
            },
            "base_line_period": {
                "range": [26, 52],
                "default": 26,
                "sensitivity": "medium"
            },
            "leading_span_period": {
                "range": [52, 104],
                "default": 52,
                "sensitivity": "low"
            }
        },
        "rsi_parameters": {
            "period": {
                "range": [7, 21],
                "default": 14,
                "sensitivity": "high"
            },
            "overbought_threshold": {
                "range": [65, 80],
                "default": 70,
                "sensitivity": "medium"
            },
            "oversold_threshold": {
                "range": [20, 35],
                "default": 30,
                "sensitivity": "medium"
            }
        },
        "market_regime_parameters": {
            "bull_market": {
                "conversion_line_period": 9,
                "base_line_period": 26,
                "rsi_period": 14,
                "overbought_threshold": 75,
                "oversold_threshold": 25
            },
            "bear_market": {
                "conversion_line_period": 14,
                "base_line_period": 52,
                "rsi_period": 21,
                "overbought_threshold": 70,
                "oversold_threshold": 30
            },
            "sideways_market": {
                "conversion_line_period": 12,
                "base_line_period": 36,
                "rsi_period": 18,
                "overbought_threshold": 65,
                "oversold_threshold": 35
            }
        },
        "risk_management": {
            "stop_loss": {
                "type": "percentage",
                "range": [1, 5],
                "default": 2,
                "unit": "%"
            },
            "take_profit": {
                "type": "percentage", 
                "range": [2, 10],
                "default": 4,
                "unit": "%"
            },
            "position_sizing": {
                "max_risk_per_trade": {
                    "range": [0.5, 2],
                    "default": 1,
                    "unit": "%"
                },
                "max_portfolio_allocation": {
                    "range": [5, 20],
                    "default": 10,
                    "unit": "%"
                }
            }
        }
    },
    "recommended_timeframes": ["4H", "1D"],
    "most_sensitive_parameters": [
        "conversion_line_period",
        "rsi_period",
        "overbought_threshold"
    ],
    "optimization_methodology": {
        "type": "grid_search",
        "walk_forward_analysis": true,
        "monte_carlo_simulations": true
    }
}
```

Key Insights:
1. Ichimoku parameters have wide ranges to capture different market dynamics
2. RSI parameters are most sensitive to market conditions
3. Risk management parameters provide flexible position sizing
4. Different parameter sets for market regimes
5. Recommended optimization uses grid search with walk-forward analysis

Recommended next steps:
- Backtest each market regime parameter set
- Use Monte Carlo simulations to validate robustness
- Continuously re-optimize based on changing market conditions
